In this video, I share something very meaningful—friends I invited from America who have come to Soweto, Jinja, not for the first time, but again. They have been here before, they saw the situation, and they chose to come back because they recognized the real need in this community.

Their return is powerful. It shows that the public health challenges in Soweto are not just temporary issues—they are ongoing and require consistent attention and action. These friends didn’t just visit and leave; they listened, they understood, and they felt the responsibility to return and be part of the solution.

As you watch this video, I encourage you to listen to their voices and experiences. They have seen firsthand the struggles with sanitation, disease risks, and living conditions, and their perspective helps highlight why this work is so important.

This is more than just a visit—it is a commitment. A commitment to raising awareness, supporting the community, and working together to bring change.

So take a moment to watch, listen, and reflect. Because sometimes, seeing the reality through the eyes of others can inspire all of us to act.
